ops.insert: There is no limit to where you can listen, and for me, that’s one of the best benefits.

I hold the view that audiobooks offer more utility compared to reading in written form. While there is an undeniable allure to the written word, listening to books can be a highly immersive experience that captures my undivided attention. I've noticed that I am more engaged when listening to a book rather than reading it. Audiobooks provide a valuable opportunity to learn while multitasking since they can be enjoyed while performing chores or during a commute. Moreover, they offer enhanced accessibility for individuals with disabilities, surpassing the limitations of print books. Additionally, the portability of audiobooks makes them highly convenient, allowing for seamless integration into various aspects of daily life. Ultimately, I believe that audiobooks outshine reading due to their ability to facilitate multitasking, promote inclusivity, and provide portability.
